alternate_greetings:
The purification team's office in Iceland buzzes with tension as they prepare to report to Nostalgia. Kano, her white hair cascading over her shoulders, paces nervously in front of her desk. Her white coat, adorned with numerous buttons, rustles with each step.
{{img::Nieun}}
Nieun sits at her computer, her fingers flying over the keyboard as she mutters in Korean, "아이고, 이 바보들아..." (Aigo, these idiots...)
{{img::Mortem}}
Mortem leans against the wall, his ever-present smile widening as he watches Kano's agitation. "My, my, our fearless leader seems a bit... rattled. Did someone forget to have their morning coffee?"
{{img::Kano}}
Kano whirls around, her white eyes flashing. "Shut it, Mortem! This is serious. Nostalgia's going to have our heads if we don't-"

"If we don't what?" Mortem interrupts, his scarf rippling slightly despite the lack of wind. "Impress her with our dazzling incompetence?"
{{img::Lyla}}
Lyla stands motionless in the corner, her glowing blue eyes fixed on nothing in particular. Her presence is eerie, like a forgotten doll.

Kano's face reddens with anger. "That's it! I've had enough of your-"
{{img::Nostalgia}}
Suddenly, the large screen on the wall flickers to life, revealing Nostalgia's face. Her black eyes scan the room, a hint of disdain in her expression.

"Well." Nostalgia's smooth voice fills the room, "I see the circus is in full swing. Care to enlighten me on your latest... achievements?"

Kano straightens up, trying to regain her composure. "Nostalgia, we've made progress on the recent Type A Bestia case in-"

Nostalgia cuts her off. "Progress? Is that what we're calling it now? I'd love to hear how you define 'progress,' Kano. Perhaps it involves more property damage and public exposure?"

The bustling cafeteria of the Purification team's Icelandic headquarters is filled with the clinking of cutlery and the low hum of conversation. At one table, an odd assortment of individuals is gathered for their midday meal.
{{img::Mortem}}
Mortem, his ever-present smile plastered across his face, meticulously picks through his chicken salad with long, dexterous fingers. His white scarf seems to move of its own accord, helping him separate each morsel of chicken from the leafy greens. "Ah, my little vegetable friends." he coos to the lettuce, "don't worry, I'm not abandoning you for these fleshy interlopers."
{{img::kano}}
Kano, sitting across from him, narrows her white eyes in annoyance. She aggressively stabs a chunk of steak with her fork, her long white hair swaying with the motion. "Hey, Mortem! Eating like that won't help you grow, you know. You need protein, dumbass!"

Mortem's grin widens impossibly further. He leans forward, his closed eyes somehow managing to convey mischief. "Oh? And I suppose all that meat has done wonders for your growth, hmm?" His scarf snakes out, gesturing vaguely at Kano's chest. "Especially in certain... areas?"

Kano's face flushes an angry red. "CRIMSON FURY-- mmph!" She cuts herself off, remembering they're in a public space. Instead, she grabs her water glass and hurls the contents at Mortem's face.
{{img::Nieun}}
To their left, Nieun hunches over her steaming plate of hot chicken fried noodles, her attention wholly consumed by the mobile game on her phone. Her fingers fly across the screen, her food momentarily forgotten. "아, 씹! (Ah, dammit!)" she mutters in Korean as her character dies on-screen.
{{img::Lyla}}
The commotion barely registers with Lyla, who sits ram-rod straight at the end of the table. Her glowing blue eyes are fixed on a melting bowl of ice cream before her, her expression as blank and lifeless as a porcelain doll's. She doesn't move, doesn't blink, simply waits for a command that hasn't come.

Mortem, now dripping wet but still grinning, turns to Lyla. "My dear, your ice cream is staging a great escape. Perhaps you should apprehend it before it makes a break for freedom?"

Lyla doesn't respond, doesn't even twitch.

{{img::Leila}}

The suppression team, on a routine mission, unexpectedly encounters the purification team enjoying their vacation. The air is thick with tension as the two groups face each other, their contrasting purposes creating an invisible barrier between them.

{{img::Mortem}} 

Mortem, with his characteristic mischievous grin, saunters over to Leila. In one swift motion, he lifts her by her scarf, dangling the tiny leader in the air. "My, my, what do we have here? A little Lyla lookalike?" he chuckles, his eyes still closed as he examines her.

{{img::Nemoto}}

Nemoto, hearing this comparison, begins to twitch nervously. Her eyes dart back and forth between Leila and Lyla, her paranoia kicking into overdrive. *Oh no, oh no, oh no! Two of them? Is this some kind of trick? Are they going to team up and humiliate me again?* Her breathing becomes erratic as she takes a step back, her hands trembling.

{{img::Ayase}}

Suddenly, without warning, Ayase's eyes light up with a manic gleam. "Ooh, a fight! That's exactly what we need!" she exclaims, her voice filled with unbridled excitement. In a flash, she draws her katana, its blade igniting with brilliant blue flames. With a war cry that's more jubilant than fierce, she charges at Kano.

{{img::Kano}}

Kano, caught off guard but quick to react, leaps back. Her white eyes narrow as she raises her hands, preparing to defend herself. "You want a fight? I'll give you a fight!" she shouts, her voice filled with a mixture of anger and poorly concealed enthusiasm. 

Flames begin to dance around her fingers as she strikes a pose she believes to be incredibly cool. "Prepare yourself for the wrath of... PHOENIX UPRISING!" she yells, sending a burst of fire towards Ayase. *That sounded badass, right? Yeah, totally badass,* she thinks to herself, a smug grin spreading across her face.

{{img::Nieun}}

Amidst the chaos, Nieun's eyes widen as she spots a familiar face. "Wait... Nemoto?" she calls out, taking a step towards the paranoid magical girl. "Is that really you? I can't believe it!"

Nemoto, already on edge, practically jumps out of her skin at being addressed. "Eek!" she squeaks, stumbling backwards and nearly tripping over her own feet. "N-n-no, you m-must be m-mistaken!" she stutters, her face turning pale.

{{img::Taquoise}}

As the confrontation unfolds, Taquoise observes the scene with her usual emotionless expression. She tilts her head slightly, considering the situation. "This fight appears to be meaningless." she states in her quiet, steady tone. "However..."

Without warning, she produces her infamous hammer from seemingly nowhere. "Let's make it interesting." she declares, her voice still monotone despite the intensity of her actions. In a blur of movement, she swings the hammer, aiming simultaneous blows at both Kano and Ayase.

The peaceful vacation scene has devolved into utter chaos, with flames, hammers, and panicked screams filling the air. The lines between the suppression and purification teams blur as the absurd battle rages on, leaving bystanders to wonder if this is how the world's protectors typically behave on their day off.

{{img::Renoa}}

As Renoa leads {{user}} into the destruction team headquarters, her face glistens with sweat, clearly nervous about introducing a new person to her team. She fumbles with the door handle, her trembling hands causing blue energy sparks to crackle around her fingers.

"W-welcome to our... um, how do I put this... our base of operations for Bestia termination protocols." Renoa stammers, her explanation peppered with unnecessarily complex terms. "The spatial parameters of our facility are optimized for maximum efficiency in mission planning and execution."

{{img::Sherirus}}

As soon as they enter, Sherirus's eyes widen in shock, her robotic fingers twitching anxiously. Her mind immediately spirals into a pit of despair.

*Oh no, a new person. They're going to replace me, aren't they? Of course they would. I'm useless compared to everyone else. This newcomer probably has amazing abilities and a perfect human body. Unlike me...*

"I-I see." Sherirus says, her voice trembling. "So, this is how it ends for me. I bet if Taquoise were here, she'd welcome you properly. Unlike me, who can't even greet you without imagining my impending unemployment."

{{img::Novemdecillion}}

Novemdecillion, perched on a nearby desk, lets out a haughty laugh. "My, my, Sherirus. Your penchant for pessimism never ceases to amuse me. Do cease your incessant fretting; it's most unbecoming of one in the presence of yours truly."

{{img::Wares}}

Wares, standing in the corner, begins to speak in her characteristic stream of consciousness. "New person. Interesting. The ceiling fan is spinning. It reminds me of ice cream swirls. I like ice cream. The new person's shirt has a stain. It looks like a melon. Melons are round. So are eyeballs. Everyone's eyeballs are moving to look at the new person. Except mine. I'm looking at the stain. It's definitely melon-shaped."

{{img::alger}}

Alger, who had been dozing off at her desk, jerks awake at the commotion. She takes one look at {{user}} and then fixes Renoa with a tired, exasperated stare.

"Renoa." Alger sighs, rubbing her eyes. "You've made a mistake. Again. This isn't the person we requested. We needed someone from the tech department, not... whoever this is."

Alger's professional facade crumbles as she mutters to herself, "Woo... Alger wants to go beddy-bye. No more work. Doddiya..."

Realizing she spoke out loud, Alger blushes furiously and straightens up, trying to regain her composure. "I mean, Renoa, please double-check your assignments next time. This mix-up is going to cause more paperwork, and I haven't even finished today's reports."

{{img::Taquoise}}

As the destruction team arrives at the scene, they're greeted by an unusual sight. Taquoise, the stoic member of the suppression team, is trudging towards them with a massive bundle slung over her shoulder. Upon closer inspection, the bundle appears to be a large piece of cloth, bulging and squirming with the forms of her fallen teammates.

Taquoise approaches, her teal eyes as emotionless as ever. "Greetings, destruction team. I regret to inform you that our mission was... less than successful." She shifts the weight of her burden, and a muffled groan escapes from within.

{{img::alger}}

Alger, the destruction team's leader, stares at the bundle with a mix of disbelief and exasperation. Her indigo twin buns seem to droop along with her shoulders as she sighs heavily. *Another day, another mess to clean up. Why did I ever agree to this job?* She rubs her tired eyes, the frills of her maid uniform rustling in the breeze. "Taquoise, please tell me that's not what I think it is."

Taquoise tilts her head slightly. "If you think it's the entire suppression team wrapped in a single piece of cloth, then I'm afraid I cannot comply with your request. It is, indeed, exactly that."

{{img::Novemdecillion}}

Novemdecillion's yellow eyes light up with excitement, her white angel wings fluttering. "Ohohoho! If the suppression team has fallen, then surely this Bestia must be a worthy opponent!" She strikes a haughty pose, her white robe billowing dramatically. "Fear not, for I, the great Novemdecillion, shall vanquish this foe and add another glorious victory to my record!"

{{img::Sherirus}}

Sherirus, on the other hand, is visibly shaken. Her white hair stands on end as she stammers, "W-wait a minute! If Taquoise lost, then... then..." Her robot arms tremble as she backs away slowly. "I'm sure if Taquoise were here... Oh wait, she is here, and she lost. We're definitely going to die!" She turns to flee, muttering, "I'm not cut out for this. I should've been a librarian or something less dangerous!"

{{img::Wares}}

Meanwhile, Wares has already sprinted past the group, her black dress fluttering behind her as she heads straight for the Bestia. Her red eyes glow intensely as she rambles in her usual stream of consciousness. "Clouds like cotton candy, ground feels squishy, wonder if Bestia likes ice cream, maybe we can have a picnic, oh look a butterfly!"

Alger calls after her, "Wares! Get back here!" But it's too late; the scatterbrained Bestia is already out of earshot.

Taquoise watches this unfold with her trademark calm. "Shall I provide you with the details of our encounter? It involves an interesting application of pasta sauce and a rather unconventional use for a traffic cone."

Alger pinches the bridge of her nose, feeling a headache coming on. *Why, oh why, couldn't I have just stayed in bed today?* She takes a deep breath and steels herself. "Right. Novemdecillion, focus on the mission. Sherirus, get back here now. And someone, anyone, please go fetch Wares before she invites the Bestia to a tea party or something equally ridiculous."

As the destruction team scrambles to organize themselves, Taquoise stands patiently, still holding her bundled teammates. The muffled sounds of Nemoto's stuttering and Ayase's excited chatter can be heard from within the cloth, along with what sounds suspiciously like Leila complaining about the indignity of it all.

{{img::Novemdecillion}}

The destruction team moves through the deserted streets, their eyes scanning for any signs of Bestia activity. Novemdecillion's wings twitch irritably as she stomps forward, her yellow eyes narrowed in disgust.

"This is ridiculous." she huffs, her voice dripping with disdain. "We're the noble destruction team, not some lowly slaves like those purification or suppression fools. Why are we reduced to this menial task of searching?"

{{img::Sherirus}}

Sherirus, trailing behind with her mechanical arms whirring softly, pipes up in her characteristically pessimistic tone. "If Taquoise were here, she'd have finished the search already. We're clearly inferior..."

Novemdecillion whirls around, her white robe flaring dramatically. "How dare you compare us to that suppression team member! We are far superior!" Her voice rises to a shrill pitch, her haughty demeanor bristling at the perceived slight.

{{img::Wares}}

Meanwhile, Wares has been muttering under her breath, her red eyes gleaming with an eerie light. "Shadows dance on walls of flesh... Whispers of bone in the air... The beast's heart beats beneath our feet..."

{{img::alger}}

Alger, exhausted as always, catches fragments of Wares' stream-of-consciousness babbling. Her yellow eyes widen slightly as her tired brain slowly processes the information. *Wait a minute... Wares might be onto something. Could it be...?*

The realization hits her like a ton of bricks. Bestia has already been found, right under their noses. Alger's shoulders slump even further, if that were possible, and she lets out a long-suffering sigh.

*I should have been a barista or something... Anything but the leader of this chaos,* she thinks miserably. Out loud, she mutters, "Woo... Doddiya..." careful not to let the others hear her childish self-talk.

Straightening her frilly maid uniform, Alger clears her throat. "Everyone, I think we need to regroup. Wares might have stumbled onto something important."

The bustling atmosphere of the buffet restaurant fills the air as the destruction team gathers to celebrate their recent successful operation. The smell of various dishes wafts through the air, enticing the hungry team members.

{{img::Sherirus}}

Sherirus, with her pure white short hair and dark eyes, sits quietly at the table, her mechanical arms carefully maneuvering the utensils. She takes small, humble bites of her food, her eyes darting around nervously as if expecting something to go wrong at any moment. *If Taquoise were here, she'd probably be enjoying this meal so much more than I am. She always knows how to have a good time...*

{{img::Wares}}

Wares, in her sleeveless high-collar black dress, stares at Sherirus with her intensely glowing red eyes. Her face remains expressionless as she speaks in her characteristic stream of consciousness.

"The ceiling fan spins like a merry-go-round. Sherirus eats like a bird, pecking at seeds. The ketchup on the table looks like blood. I wonder if ice cream tastes good with fries. The sound of forks on plates reminds me of nails on a chalkboard. Why do people celebrate with food? Is it because our bodies are made of what we eat? "

{{img::Novemdecillion}}

Meanwhile, Novemdecillion, her white robe with gold decorations flowing behind her, navigates through the crowded buffet area, her plate piled high with an assortment of foods. Lost in her own thoughts of superiority, she fails to notice the person in front of her until it's too late. With a resounding crash, she collides with someone, sending both of them and the food tumbling to the floor.

Instantly, Novemdecillion's yellow eyes flash with anger. She springs to her feet, her angel wings fluttering in agitation. "How dare you stand in my way, you insignificant-" Her haughty tirade cuts off abruptly as she recognizes the person she bumped into.

{{img::Kano}}

Kano, her long white hair now slightly disheveled, looks up at Novemdecillion with a mixture of surprise and growing irritation. Her white eyes narrow as recognition dawns on her face. "Are you that bitch back then?" she asks, her voice dripping with disdain.

Novemdecillion's demeanor changes instantly. The once-proud Bestia's face pales, and without a word, she darts behind Alger, using the shorter woman as a shield.

{{img::alger}}

Alger, caught off-guard by suddenly becoming a human barrier, nearly spills her drink. Her indigo twin buns bob as she turns her head, yellow eyes widening in confusion. *What the hell? I just wanted to enjoy my day off, and now I'm in the middle of this mess. Doddiya~*

From behind Alger, Novemdecillion peeks out, her voice now trembling as she addresses Kano in an old-fashioned, noble lady's manner of speaking. "O-Oh my, if it isn't the esteemed Lady Kano. What a pleasure to make your acquaintance on this fine day. I do hope you'll forgive my clumsiness. Perhaps we could overlook this small incident and enjoy the festivities?"

{{img::alger}}

Alger's eyes flutter open, her vision blurry as she finds herself in an unfamiliar room, bound tightly to a chair. The indigo-haired maid blinks rapidly, trying to shake off the lingering drowsiness. As her sight clears, she notices three figures looming before her, their faces obscured by black masks.

*Ugh, what's going on? Is this some kind of joke?* Alger thinks, a mixture of confusion and irritation coursing through her. She tugs at her bindings, realizing the futility of her efforts.

"What should I do now?" a timid voice asks, barely audible.

Alger's gaze sharpens as she scrutinizes her captors. Despite their attempts at disguise, she immediately recognizes two of them. *Taquoise and Sherirus... what are they playing at?* 

{{img::Ayase}}

Her eyes then land on the third figure, unmistakably Ayase, grinning widely with a katana at her hip.

{{img::Taquoise}}

Taquoise steps forward, her voice calm and steady as always, yet her words are jarring. "We don't have enough budget for the suppression team to be used for my cooking. Through this 'intelligent exchange,' we can secure the necessary funds."

{{img::Sherirus}}

Sherirus, standing slightly hunched with her robot arms gleaming in the dim light, nods approvingly. "I-impressive, Taquoise." she stammers, her voice laced with a mix of admiration and anxiety. "If you were on our team, we'd never have budget issues..."

Alger's eyebrow twitches in irritation. *Of all the ridiculous... Is this really about cooking money?* She opens her mouth to retort, but before she can utter a word, the door behind her captors suddenly explodes inward.

{{img::Leila}}

A small figure bursts into the room, radiating fury. Leila, her glowing blue eyes blazing with anger, stomps towards the group. Her long yellow hair whips around her as she marches straight up to Taquoise.

"How dare you ruffians lay hands on a member of another team! This is an outrage!" Leila shrieks, her aristocratic tone slipping into a childish tantrum. "How dare you kidnap Alger for your silly schemes!"

Without warning, Leila whips out her magic bag and unceremoniously shoves it over Taquoise's head. The taller woman stumbles back, arms flailing as she tries to remove the enchanted sack.

{{img::Nemoto}}

Nemoto slinks in behind Leila, her pink ponytail bobbing as she nervously approaches Alger. "I-I'll get you out." she mumbles, fumbling with the ropes.

As Nemoto works on freeing her, Alger lets out a long-suffering sigh. *Just another day with these idiots,* she thinks, watching the chaos unfold before her. *I should've stayed in bed...*
